Peru Stocks: Rio Alto, La Cima, Candente, Volcan, Relapasa

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-15T18:23:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/peru-stocks-rio-alto-la-cima-candente-volcan-relapasa.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:13 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index dropped 2.3 percent to 20,955.26.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 1.6 percent to 2,918.00.  Gold miners dropped after futures slumped and a slide in
U.S. stocks sent the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index to the lowest
level since January, said Daniel Romero, an analyst at Lima-
based investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.    Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration
company, fell 6.1 percent to $2.15. Gold Fields La Cima SA
(LACIMAI1 PE), a unit of Gold Fields Ltd., slid 3.5 percent to
3.04 soles.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer
with a gold mine in Peru, fell 3.3 percent to $1.45.  Copper, zinc and tin miners dropped as metals declined in
New York and  London .    Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, fell 5.3 percent to 18 cents. Volcan Cia.
Minera SAA (VOLCAAC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, dropped
4.8 percent to 4 soles.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a
Canadian exploration company, fell 4.5 percent to $1.70.  Minsur
SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer,
declined 4.6 percent to 4.19 soles.  Fuel refiners fell after crude dropped to a two-week low in
New York.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, fell for a sixth session, losing 3.7 percent to
1.85 soles.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, dropped 2 percent to $1.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
